<center>'''Level 678''' is the 679<sup>th</sup> level of The Backrooms.</center>

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

==<center>> Description <</center>==

Level 678, also known as Infinite Ducts, appears to be a series of air conditioning ducts with no dead ends. Some ducts are full and irregular, while others are circular, triangular, or have other shapes.

{{blurimage|file=Level 678 Image 2.webp|caption=A fork at level 678.}}

The Infinite Ducts appear to have non-Euclidean geometry, with some exhibiting peculiarities. Apparently, some have dented walls, and due to the vastness of level 678, it is unlikely that a wanderer will encounter anyone else roaming the level.

Some parts of the level appear to be so full of dust that it is impossible to walk because of the dust covering everything, so, due to the non-Euclidean nature of the level, it ends up creating shortcuts and other routes. Some ducts seem to go up or down. The ducts seem to shrink, grow, or become very narrow.

Level 678 was created after a separation; it used to be Level 2.84, so it retains some aspects of that level. To date, it is not known what caused the separation of level 678. Some parts of the level appear to be quite dangerous, with some ducts compressing so much that they tear through the walls that make up the level, creating a hole that apparently leads to an air duct room.

The room, commonly called the Duct Base, appears to be a room with several intertwined ducts, contains a lot of dust, and some ducts seem to have an end. It is possible to see several fans in this room, and a light coming from them seems to have no source, but leads to another room. It is possible to see a lamp on the ceiling that looks new and modern, even though the room looks like a duct room from the 1970s.

At this level, sounds of banging are often heard from the ducts, as well as sounds similar to something crawling through them. There have even been reports of pathways closing behind people, as though the ducts were moving around. Additionally, the ducts could also change the color of their walls, appear more rusty, and feel damp and sweltering.

==<center>> Colonies & Outposts <</center>==
Due to the nature of level 678, it is not possible to establish bases, outposts, or colonies.

==<center>> Addenda <</center>==

<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Recovered Note</span><center>'''<big>Crazy Ducts</big>'''</center><br/>
<center>Note found by {{USERNAME|Special:My Page}}</center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<br>I was on [[Level 2]], and I ended up entering a common air duct on [[Level 2]].

At first, I thought it was an exit from [[Level 2]], and... It really is!

Good. Apparently, this level is a series of endless ducts; it's very hot due to the high energy. It seems that some ducts are triangular, others pentagonal, or completely circular. Some also have a lot of accumulated dust. This pen will probably melt at some point, so some parts may be a little blurred, but I don't think it will interfere too much.

{{blurimage|file=Level 678 image.jpg|caption=A duct infested with dust}}

Well, but what I really want to write about is a crazy theory of mine.

Well. This theory can explain the crumpled parts of the air ducts.

Due to the heat produced by the high amount of energy, there ends up being a spike because of some intervention, and due to the heat spike, which is caused by large amounts of molecules moving at high speed, they end up coming together and getting faster, creating these spikes that cause a lot of dust. This dust ends up accumulating and putting weight on the steel of the duct, which ends up being dented; that's why we see some dents in the walls that make up the ducts.

Or it could also be an entity that pursues the wanderer at such a high speed that if there is a curve and the wanderer turns and runs around that curve, the Crawlers end up hitting with such force that they dent the walls of the duct.</br>

<div style="text-align: right;"><blockquote>''- Barney Swelmond, 09/01/1939''</blockquote></div>
