<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Recovered Note</span><center>'''<big>I can't see him</big>'''</center><br/>

<center>Note found by the [[A.A.E.G.]].</center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

<br>I have been in these ducts for a while now, and I'm just not sure what to do anymore. They feel infinite—it is like being in endless suffering. It is all damp here, and it is also really hot. It's suffocating being here, and the only way to endure it is to crawl through these ducts. I did hear sounds, so I know there must be something else that has been crawling around here, too.
{{blurimage|file=iiow.png|caption=I can’t see him }}
I had just come from [[Level 154]]. I was looking through some places in that level and went inside some of the ducts, and now look—I am here. I'm reasonably certain that this is a level of some sort, perhaps a sub-level of [[Level 2]] or [[Level 3]], or maybe a completely new level. I just have to keep crawling through here.

Time's gone by, and the sounds keep intensifying. I yelled for help—maybe someone else is stuck here and could help. But now I'm not sure; there’s been no answer. All I hear is it getting closer... Somehow, it’s coming toward me. I can only hope it's someone coming to help me escape.

I JUST CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE. I can't keep crawling through this crap. What if I just gave up and waited to die?

A couple of hours ago, I saw it. I saw someone, but it wasn’t a person. It was a THING, and ever since, I have been seeing it sort of lurking, peeking at me from the end of a duct or the corner of my eye. I am scared, and I don’t want to keep moving forward. I feel like it changes shape. Sometimes it has eyes, sometimes it has no eyes but has an elongated neck. I don’t even know what the fuck it is anymore.

I’ve come to terms with it. I don’t believe I’m going to escape from here. There it is at the end of the duct, glaring into my eyes, and it won’t go away. Just like always, it’s right there, completely unmoving, acting as if it is not participating in anything. I’m freaking out. I’m so fatigued, I’m going to keep crawling toward it. The more I move toward it, the less I am able to see it. Now it feels as if I can’t see him anymore.

Hold on… I just felt something behind my ankle…</br>

<div style="text-align: right;"><blockquote>''- Jane Doe, 3/07/2001''</blockquote></div>
----</div>


==<center>> Entities <</center>==

<center><big><big>Crawlers</big></big></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{blurimage|file=Crawlers.jpg|caption=A sketch of a Crawler.}}

Crawlers, scientifically known as Rastejiantus Anormius. Have wrinkled gray skin, red eyes, and deformed mouths, with no visible nose or pupils. On their chests, they have red stripes that originate from the heart, although no audible heartbeat can be detected. They have extremely elongated arms and hands with pointed fingers, and they walk with heavy steps. Their feet are strange, with six-pointed toes and reduced size, seeming to merge with the ground. Crawlers' feet have evolved to allow movement in confined spaces, making them agile in claustrophobic environments.

Crawlers attack humans through psychological disturbances, including hallucinations, whispers, and disturbances. However, the most lethal effect is the change in heart rate, which causes blood clotting and eventually the death of the wanderer.

Crawlers are believed to be the result of an infection caused by a [[Entity 8|Hound]] attack on a previously infected and treated wanderer. The wanderer's immune system collapsed after a second attack, leading to unsuccessful experiments by [[XONE Laboratories|XONE]].

Crawlers have a wild and unique nature. After spotting a wanderer, it advances and crawls at a speed close to that of a cheetah. After getting close, it stands still and forces the wanderer to watch. Little is known about the nature of Crawlers, but it is believed that they are a creation of the levels themselves, so that there is no safe place for wanderers to hide.

It’s more common to find Crawlers in tighter spaces, typically crawling through the ducts. It is not really understood how they do this, yet when they see a victim, they can suddenly disappear and then reappear somewhere else in the level; they can appear in front of or behind the victim. They employ this as a means to psychologically attack their target.

<center><big><big>Clumps</big></big></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

[[Entity 5|Clumps]] live in some parts of the level, but they are very difficult to find. If someone finds them, the wanderer needs to cut through, as they block some parts of the level, requiring shortcuts. Since the level never has dead ends, there may be other shortcuts.

